Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: gVXR
Version: 2.0.6
Summary: gVirtualXray (gVXR) Bindings to simulate realist X-ray attenuation images in microseconds from triangle meshes.
Home-page: https://gvirtualxray.sourceforge.io/
Author: Dr Franck P. Vidal
License: UNKNOWN
Platform: UNKNOWN
Requires-Python: >=3.6
License-File: LICENSE

The gVXR Bindings project allows to use of the gVirtualXray (gVXR), the Virtual X-Ray Imaging Library on GPU with python. It allows the user to simulate realist X-ray attenuation images in microseconds from triangle meshes. This project is still experimental. For more information, please visit https://gvirtualxray.sourceforge.io/

